{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Missing required key from both file and environment reports exact config path (e.g., `database.host`).","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"A pure unit test of only validation logic can miss failures in how file values and `TOOL_` env overrides are merged before validation. The real failure boundary is the composed loader path (read YAML + read env + merge + validate + format error). No external network/subprocess is needed.","test_description":"Create a temp config file that omits `database.host`, clear related `TOOL_` env vars, run the real loader entrypoint, assert it fails and the emitted message contains the exact dotted path `database.host`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"`XDG_CONFIG_HOME` changes config resolution root from `~/.config` to that directory.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk is in wiring env lookup and path resolution into the loader. A unit test of a path helper may miss loader-level mistakes (wrong precedence/order). This is local env+filesystem composition, not external infra.","test_description":"Set `XDG_CONFIG_HOME` to a temp directory containing `tool/config.yaml`, ensure `~/.config/tool/config.yaml` has a different sentinel value (or is absent), run loader, and assert it reads the file under `XDG_CONFIG_HOME`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"`TOOL_` environment variable overrides conflicting YAML file key.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Mocking either source can hide precedence bugs in the actual merge pipeline (name mapping, type coercion, override order). The minimum realistic boundary is both real inputs wired through the loader.","test_description":"Write a temp YAML config with a key (e.g., `database.host: file-host`), set corresponding `TOOL_` env var to `env-host`, invoke loader, and assert resulting config value is `env-host`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"YAML syntax error reports detected line number in error output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Correctness depends on behavior of the real YAML parser and exception-to-message mapping. Mocking parser errors would likely always pass and miss real parser line/format differences.","test_description":"Provide an invalid YAML file with a known broken line, run loader, assert failure message includes that line number (or parser-reported location) and is actionable.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"If config directory is missing on startup, loader creates it and writes defaults before continuing.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is about real filesystem side effects (mkdir + file write + subsequent load). In-process mocks can miss ordering and actual write-path bugs. External services/subprocesses are not required.","test_description":"Start with an isolated temp HOME/XDG location where config dir does not exist, run loader startup, assert directory now exists, defaults file was created with expected baseline keys, and loader proceeds without fatal error.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
